nt that $\\cos n \\theta = r.$ Then the complementary event $A_n^c$ is that $\\cos n \\theta$ is irrational. Let $A$ be the event that $\\cos k \\theta$ is irrational for at least one $k$ such that $2 \\leq k \\leq n.$ Then $A$ can be written as the union of the events $A_k^c,$ so by the inclusion-exclusion principle, \\[\\begin{aligned}\\mathbb{P}(A) &= \\sum_{2 \\leq k \\leq n} \\mathbb{P}(A_k^c) - \\sum_{2 \\leq k < j \\leq n} \\mathbb{P}(A_k^c \\cap A_j^c) + \\sum_{2 \\leq k < j < l \\leq n} \\mathbb{P}(A_k^c \\cap A_j^c \\cap A_l^c) - \\cdots \\\\ &= \\sum_{2 \\leq k \\leq n} \\mathbb{P}(A_k^c) - \\sum_{2 \\leq k < j \\leq n} \\mathbb{P}(A_k^c \\cap A_j^c) + \\sum_{2 \\leq k < j < l \\leq n} \\mathbb{P}(A_k^c \\cap A_j^c \\cap A_l^c) - \\cdots\\end{aligned}\\]\nWe have \\[\\begin{aligned}\\mathbb{P}(A_k^c) &= 1 - \\mathbb{P}(A_k) \\\\ &= 1 - \\mathbb{P}(A_k \\subseteq A)\\\\ \n&= 1 - \\sum_{r \\in \\mathbb{Q}} \\mathbb{P}(A_k \\cap A_r) \\\\ &= 1 - \\sum_{r \\in \\mathbb{Q}} \\mathbb{P}(A_k^c \\cap A_r^c) \\\\ &= 1 - \\sum_{r \\in \\mathbb{Q}} \\left(\\frac{1}{2} - \\left| \\cos (k \\theta) - r \\right|\\right) \\\\ &= \\begin{cases}\\frac{1}{2} & \\text{if $\\cos (k \\theta)$ is irrational} \\\\ 0 & \\text{if $\\cos (k \\theta)$ is rational}\\end{cases}\\end{aligned},\\]so $\\mathbb{P}(A_k^c) = \\begin{cases}\\frac{1}{2} & \\text{if $\\cos (k \\theta)$ is irrational} \\\\ 0 & \\text{if $\\cos (k \\theta)$ is rational}\\end{cases}.$</think> <answer>$8$</answer>", "truth": "4", "reward_format": 1.0, "reward_answer": 0.0, "reward_total": 0.0}, {"prompt": "A conversation between User and Assistant. The User asks a question, and the Assistant solves it. The Assistant first thinks about the reasoning process in the mind and then provides the User with the answer. The reasoning process is enclosed within <think> </think> and answer is enclosed within <answer> </answer> tags, respectively, i.e., <think> reasoning process here </think> <answer> answer here </answer>.\n